@PayAdaIO The key to success will be the integration of stablecoins such as USDCx. However, transferring Cardano Native Tokens (CNT) from one wallet to another still requires the minimum ADA amount to be included in the transaction if the transaction partners do not consolidate their UTXOs.

I described this issue last year and published both a solution and the corresponding code. With this approach, transferring USDCx (or other CNTs) only incurs the standard network transaction fee.

ADA itself is likely to remain volatile in the future. Therefore, price listings in stores must always take the current exchange rate into account when converting prices, which can create additional operational effort and potentially extra costs.

